TRIP is defined in RFC 3219.  It was originally used by telephone gateway
to announce the telephone numbers it serves.
A TRIP speaker makes announcements and a TRIP listener receives announcements.

TRIP has an external part (ETRIP) and an internal part (ITRIP).
For VOD, we only need the latter.

TRIP has 4 messages:
OPEN: to initiate a T RIP session
UPDATE: for HFC topology change updage
NOTIFICATION: for error notification
KEEPALIVE: for resource manager failure detection

VREP (Video Registration Protocol)
  used between:
    - data plane devices and resource managers,
    - resource managers and redirectors

VRIP (Video Routing over IP)
  used between redirectors in different streaming zones


